  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SENIOR HUMAN RESOURCE (GENERALIST)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Senior HR Executive (Generalist)</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Salary: </strong>$3,500 – $4,500 (depending on experience)</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Working Hours: </strong>8:30am – 5:30pm (Monday - Friday)</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Benefits: </strong>15 Days AL, Performance Bonus</li></ul><ul><li>2 months once Travel to India for project purposes </li></ul><p><strong>Job Summary:</strong></p><p>Support the HR & Admin Manager in handling the <strong>full spectrum of HR</strong> and administrative functions, ensuring smooth HR operations and compliance with Singapore employment laws.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities：</strong></p><ul><li><p>Handle recruitment, payroll, leave, compensation & benefits</p></li><li><p>Process payroll and statutory submissions</p></li><li><p>Manage employee lifecycle (onboarding to exit)</p></li><li><p>Maintain employee records and HR documentation</p></li><li><p>Assist in performance reviews and training coordination</p></li><li><p>Organize employee engagement activities</p></li><li><p>Support daily HR and administrative operations</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><ul><li><p><strong>Able to start immediately or with one month’s notice.</strong></p></li><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Human Resources or related field</p></li><li><p>Minimum 1–3 years of HR generalist experience</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Singapore employment laws & work pass application</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Chinese as the role is required to prepare reports in Chinese</p></li><li><p><strong>Comfortable to travel to India for project purposes (2 months once)</strong></p></li></ul></li></ul><p>Applicants who possess relevant experience for the above responsibilities are most welcome to apply. If you do not possess the above experience, your application will still be considered on individual merits and you may be contacted for other opportunities.<br />Please submit your updated resume in MS Words format by using the APPLY NOW BUTTON.</p><p>**We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates would be notified.</p><p>By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by company relating to this job application.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.mci.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MCI-Job-Applicant-Data-Protection-Notice.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.mci.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MCI-Job-Applicant-Data-Protection-Notice.pdf</a></p><p><strong>Yong Jia Wen</strong></p><p><br /><strong>Registration Number: R25146805</strong><br /><strong>EA Licence No: 13C6730 (MCI CONSULTING PTE. LTD)</strong></p>",
